---
title: Sizzling Southwestern Chicken with a Sweet Potato, Bell Pepper, and Feta Jumble
description: Red and yellow peppers, orange sweet potatoes, scallion greens and lime—okay, so we might be missing the BIV part of ROYGBIV, but the first four letters are well-represented on this plate. The bright and colorful veggie jumble is bursting with concentrated, oven-roasted flavors, while the spice-rubbed chicken breasts on top bring plenty of Southwestern flair.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sizzling-southwestern-chicken-de2034b2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sizzling-southwestern-chicken-b617337c.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: North America
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sizzling-southwestern-chicken-59318e5551d3f10d1b41e3c2
nutrition:
  calories: 530 kcal
  fat: 15 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 550 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Peel @sweet potatoes{2}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender, about ~{25%minutes} total (we'll be adding more items to the sheet after 10 minutes).

Core and seed @red bell pepper{1} and @yellow bell pepper{1}, then cut into 1-inch squares. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Zest @lime{1} into a #medium bowl{}, then cut into halves.

Add @Southwest spice blend{1%teaspoon} and a large drizzle of @olive oil{} to bowl with zest and stir to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then rub spice mixture into meat. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until no longer pink in center, about ~{5%minutes} per side.

Once sweet potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Give sweet potatoes a toss and push toward one side of sheet. Add bell peppers to other side of sheet. Return sheet to oven and roast until both are tender, about ~{12-15%minutes} more.

Once sweet potatoes and bell peppers are done, add to another medium bowl along with scallion whites, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt, pepper, and more lime juice (to taste).

Thinly slice chicken. Divide jumble between plates, then top with chicken. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.